comments.body:
@rhatdan Portable Batch System
basically if user wants to compute something that will take a long time/lot of resources, they submit their script to PBS which then decides when/on which server to run the script (based on current load on the servers). Then when the job is finished, output of the script is saved in the user's home directory and all temporary files are cleaned up.

The problem is that when podman changes CGroup to user's user.slice PBS can't keep track of the processes spawned from within podman, so it can't properly monitor resource use or clean up after itself
